Two fixes: 1) MCP servers weren't responding as subprocesses because Python's stdout is block-buffered when piped. sys.stdout.write() + flush() wasn't enough — switched to sys.stdout.buffer.write() + buffer.flush() which bypasses text-mode buffering entirely. This was likely the root cause of the CLI never loading xpressclaw MCP tools. 2) Disallowed AskUserQuestion — bypassPermissions auto-skips it, so the agent continues without waiting for user input.
